# gherkin-review.goals

*Output of the Goal Storming session held 2026-07-12 (owner + LLM). Goals ratified
by the owner. This is the first dogfood unit — vdd-loop building its own next
skill through its own loop. Friction observed along the way is logged in
`field-notes.md`.*

## Goals

- 🟩 **G1** — An author of a `.feature` can find and fix what's wrong with their
  verification standard without rereading the guidelines: every finding is
  located, explained, and traceable to a specific guideline section.
- 🟩 **G2** — Defects that would corrupt the downstream loop (unverifiable `Then`
  steps, RED scenarios that don't assert the absence of the forbidden effect,
  malformed `@eval` lines) are caught before the coding agent builds against
  the standard.
- 🟩 **G3** — A "no blocking findings" verdict is meaningful: the review can
  genuinely fail a bad standard — it never rubber-stamps.

## Verification intent

- **G1** → deterministic: seeded-defect fixtures — each seeded violation must
  appear in the findings, located and citing the right guideline section
  (YELLOW, checked mechanically against a fixture manifest). Judgment: whether
  findings are fixable *from their text alone* → `@eval` E1 (Actionability).
- **G2** → deterministic: the fixture set includes exactly the loop-corrupting
  defect classes (vague `Then`, RED-without-absence, malformed `@eval`) — same
  YELLOW fixture checks cover it.
- **G3** → deterministic: the clean exemplar must yield zero must-fix findings
  *while the seeded fixtures yield at least one each* — the pair together proves
  the verdict can go both ways. Judgment: findings separate must-fix from noise
  → `@eval` E2 (Signal).
- Cross-cutting: no invented rules — deterministic floor (every cited section
  must exist in the guidelines, RED) under a judgment bar (the explanation
  faithfully represents what the section says, `@eval` E3 gate).

**Layer ruling from the session (owner):** the Validation/Evaluation split is
defined by the *nature of the check*, not by what executes the subject. "The
findings report contains the seeded defect" is mechanically assertable → YELLOW,
even though an LLM produces the report. Run-to-run variance of the LLM subject is
a test-engineering concern (protocol), not grounds to demote the check to the
Evaluation layer.

## Design Concept *(🟪)*

> A lint pass for your verification standard — it tells you where the standard
> can't be trusted, and never touches it.

## Constraints *(⬛)*

*vdd-loop has no `SPEC.md` of its own (see field-notes) — the constraint surface
for this unit is `skills/README.md`, the family contract:*

- The skill conforms to the shared SKILL.md family format (frontmatter +
  Purpose / Inputs / Outputs / Invariants / Procedure / Composes with; no Stop
  conditions — it is not a looping skill).
- It reviews the **complete** standard: Gherkin scenarios *and* `@eval` lines
  (it is the primary reviewer; `rubric-review` is the narrower sibling for
  `.rubric.md` detail files).
- **Report-only.** It never mutates the artifact under review.
- It ends by stating what it produced and *offering* the next station — never
  auto-invoking another skill.
